The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, August 17, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority has notified revised prices of three bulk drugs. Price of Glipizide has been increased to Rs 31,584 per kg from Rs 29,744 per kg, Dextropropoxyphene HCL to Rs 3,997 per kg from Rs 3,748 per kg and the price of Dextroproppoxyphene Napsylate has been fixed at Rs 5,357 per kg, an official release said.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The government has decided to close two deposit schemes from September 13. The deposit scheme for retiring government employees of 1989 and deposit scheme for retiring employees of PSU firms of 1991, maturing on or before September 13, shall cease to earn any interest after that date, the finance ministry said.																								 Stuttgart, Aug. 16: DaimlerChrysler today said it has sold its 10.5 per cent stake in South Korean car manufacturer Hyundai for over $900 million. 																								 Mumbai, Aug. 16: Essar Steel Ltd today reported a 392 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 50.44 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 against Rs 10.25 crore a year-ago.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Indian Airlines has ruled out any immediate rise in air fares despite the increase in fuel costs.
